# New HTSA enrollment page — fast path

**Never** edit an existing client's `htsa-enrollment-*.html` to create a new one. **Always** duplicate a **gold** template with `cp`, then only replace the personalized fields.

## 1. Legacy invoices are frozen

- Do **not** retrofit, mass-edit, or “clean up” past `htsa-enrollment-*.html` files already created or sent.
- Do **not** change legacy pages unless **CJ explicitly asks** for that **specific** file (one-off update).
- **Margarita De La Rosa** (`htsa-enrollment-margarita-de-la-rosa.html`) is the **first real client invoice** using the **new Terms agreement gate**.
- Sandbox / rehearsal only: **`htsa-enrollment-cj-clay-practice.html`** (not a production client invoice template for copy-paste blindly—see Terms gate notes below).

## 2. What CJ supplies for NEW invoices

For every **new** page, confirm:

- Full name  
- Email  
- Phone  
- **Program type:** Closer **or** Setter **or** both (Closer & Setter)  
- **Orange performance guarantee box:** yes / no (**see §3**)  
- **Payment setup:** in-house cash only **or** in-house cash **plus** financing (ClarityPay / Flexxbuy-style blocks as applicable)  
- Any **special note** CJ explicitly requested (capture verbatim; add only where asked)

Optional: client slug (`firstname-lastname`, lowercase).

## 3. “Guarantee yes/no” means only the orange banner

When CJ says **performance guarantee**, that refers **only** to the optional **orange** `.enrollment-guarantee-banner` block.

- It does **not** mean the normal **Terms of Service agreement** gate (PDF + checklist + acknowledgment + Sheets).
- Guarantee **yes** → include the orange banner (copy pattern from approved gold examples such as **`htsa-enrollment-timi-bonner-mccourt.html`** as **read-only** reference).
- Guarantee **no** → omit that orange block on **new** builds. Do **not** remove or rewrite Terms-gate behavior to “compensate.”

Supporting “Performance Guarantee. HTSA stands behind…” wording belongs **inside** that orange banner on guarantee-**yes** **new** invoices—not as a substitute for Margarita-style Terms wording, and **not** by rewriting legacy invoices.

## 4. Terms agreement gate — standard on NEW invoices

The Terms gate ships **before** payment / financing buttons unlock. It includes:

- **Terms PDF** link (full Terms of Service).  
- **Lifetime Access** / **coaching** / **AI platform** clarification copy (aligned with **`htsa-enrollment-margarita-de-la-rosa.html`**).  
- Checkbox acknowledgment + button to record agreement.  
- **Google Apps Script:** posts to the **existing deployed web-app endpoint** configured on the page; **logs to the enrollment Sheet**. It records **Terms acknowledgment only**—**it does not state or imply that payment was completed.**  

**Do not** put the CJ practice **simulated payment** / trial-pay lab flow on **real client** invoice pages. That flow exists **only** on **`htsa-enrollment-cj-clay-practice.html`**.

Structural reference after the gate: **`htsa-enrollment-margarita-de-la-rosa.html`** (live) and **`htsa-enrollment-cj-clay-practice.html`** (sandbox). After **Welcome to the HTSA Family**, flow continues to testimonials / footer—no duplicate Terms block underneath.

## 5. NEW invoice workflow (delivery)

1. Pick the **correct gold template** for program + pricing pattern (often start from **`htsa-enrollment-margarita-de-la-rosa.html`** for the Terms gate + investment layout).
2. **`cp`** to **`htsa-enrollment-{firstname}-{lastname}.html`** (new filename—never overwrite another client).
3. Change **only** name, email, phone, program, payment-required fields, slug/data attributes on the Terms gate panel, plus any CJ-requested specials.
4. **`grep`** the new file: **zero** hits for old template-first names unless intentional.
5. Smoke-check Terms gate: checkbox → record posts to Sheets (Apps Script reachable); unlock works; **payment** still means real checkout links on prod pages—not the practice simulator.
6. **Commit/push:** include **only** the **new invoice** file (`git add path/to/htsa-enrollment-newclient.html`) and any **shared rule/skill** updates made in the same task—**never** bulk-add unrelated HTML.
7. Return **only** the clean client-facing URL:

   `https://closewithcjclay.com/htsa-enrollment-{firstname}-{lastname}.html`

**No** `?v=` cache-busting query unless **CJ explicitly asks**.

## 6. What not to stage or commit

- Do **not** `git add` **`Untitled`**, **`HTSA-Terms-of-Service-cleaned-review.html`**, **`HTSA-Terms-of-Service-cleaned-review.pdf`**, or other unrelated scratch/review artifacts.
- Do **not** stage or commit **legacy** invoice HTML except when CJ deliberately updates that single file.

**Do not** add “3 one-on-one sessions with Chad” unless the user **explicitly** asks.

## Meaning of legacy vs new — quick reference

- **Orange guarantee** (`enrollment-guarantee-banner`) = CJ’s explicit **yes/no**, separate from Terms.  
- **Terms gate** = standard on **new** invoices; gates **payment buttons** until recorded.

